</head>
<body>

   

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🥣 Sabudana Khichdi</h1>
       

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 cup Sabudana (Tapioca Pearls)</li>
            <li>1 medium Potato (boiled & diced)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup Peanuts (roasted & crushed)</li>
            <li>1 Green Chili (chopped)</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>8-10 Curry Leaves</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Ghee or Oil</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>1 tsp Lemon Juice</li>
            <li>Fresh Coriander for garnish</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>

        <h3>Step 1: Soak Sabudana</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Wash sabudana and soak in water for 4-5 hours or overnight.</li>
            <li>Drain excess water and let it rest for 30 minutes.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 2: Cook the Khichdi</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Heat ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds.</li>
            <li>Add curry leaves and chopped green chilies. Sauté for a few seconds.</li>
            <li>Add diced potatoes and cook until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Mix in the soaked sabudana and crushed peanuts.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and stir-fry for 5-7 minutes.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Step 3: Serve</h3>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Turn off the heat and add lemon juice.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander and serve hot!</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
